<!doctype html>
<!--
  adopter-welcome.step-6.mjml — Month 3: an offer of self.
  Source: Drip Emails for adopter Sign-up.docx (Email 7).
-->
<html><body style="font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 640px; margin: 0 auto; color: #1f2937;">
  <h2 style="color: #1f2937;">An Offer of Self</h2>
  <p>Hi {{ contact_display_name }},</p>

  <p>
    God's plan to reach Frontier People Groups is to use Christ followers.
    Where do you fit?
  </p>

  <h3 style="color: #374151;">A Prayer of Love and Belief</h3>
  <p>
    Lord, I stand before You today and confess that You are good. Your
    heart is merciful. I believe that Jesus is the Way, the Truth, and the
    Life, and that His words are the only hope for a broken world. I believe
    that the Great Commission is not a suggestion for a few, but a command
    for all who follow You. Because I love You, I want what You want.
  </p>

  <h3 style="color: #374151;">The "Here I Am" Prayer</h3>
  <p>
    In Isaiah 6:8, the prophet heard the voice of the Lord saying, "Whom
    shall I send? And who will go for us?" Isaiah responded with five simple
    words: "Here am I. Send me!"
  </p>
  <p>
    Today, I make that same offer. I am not my own; I was bought with a
    price. I lay down my plans, my career goals, and my personal comforts.
    Lord, if You want me to go to the Frontier, I will go. If You want me to
    stay and fund those who go, I will give. If You want me to spend my life
    mobilizing others, I will speak.
  </p>

  <h3 style="color: #374151;">Inviting the Holy Spirit</h3>
  <p>
    Holy Spirit, I invite Your conviction. If there is any selfishness in me,
    wash it away. If I have been indifferent to the lost, change my heart. I
    ask for Your direction. Guide my steps and show me exactly how I fit
    into Your global mission. Transform my "personal life mission" from
    self-seeking to Kingdom-building.
  </p>

  <h3 style="color: #374151;">A Commitment to the Frontier</h3>
  <p>
    I commit to being a part of reaching the Frontier People Groups however
    You see fit. Whether through my prayers, my pockets, or my presence, I
    want to be a vessel of Your light. Let my life be a testimony of Your
    grace until every tribe, tongue, and nation knows that Jesus is Lord.
  </p>
  <p>Amen.</p>

  <p>The Joshua Project Team</p>

  <p style="color: #9ca3af; font-size: 12px; margin-top: 32px;">
    Reply "unsubscribe" to stop receiving this series.
  </p>
</body></html>
